MAYA: UNGH!

214
00:10:02,561 --> 00:10:04,146
(CHAIR SMASHES,
MAYA GRUNTS)

215
00:10:04,229 --> 00:10:06,023
GLORIA:
SO WHAT EXACTLY
IS THIS ESCAPE PLAN?

216
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:08,442
(MAYA SMASHES THE CHAIR,
PIECES CLATTER)

217
00:10:10,444 --> 00:10:12,070
MAYA:
I PLAY SICK.

218
00:10:12,154 --> 00:10:13,447
YOU CALL THE GUY INTO THE ROOM,
WORRIED ABOUT ME.

219
00:10:13,530 --> 00:10:15,032
AND WHEN HE LEAST
EXPECTS IT,

220
00:10:15,115 --> 00:10:16,950
YOU'RE GONNA HIT HIM
OVER THE HEAD WITH THIS...

221
00:10:17,034 --> 00:10:18,577
AND HARD.

222
00:10:20,412 --> 00:10:22,748
(WOODEN PIECES CLATTER)

223
00:10:26,251 --> 00:10:27,085
GLORIA:
HELP! (BANGS ON DOOR)
HELP!

224
00:10:32,674 --> 00:10:35,594
(APPROACHING FOOTSTEPS)

225
00:10:35,677 --> 00:10:37,846
HEY! WE'RE ALL TRYING
TO FIND MAYA. GONNA HELP?

226
00:10:37,930 --> 00:10:39,640
WHAT IF I NEVER
SEE HIM AGAIN?

227
00:10:39,723 --> 00:10:41,767
WINSTON?
HE'S JUST IN THE OTHER-

228
00:10:41,850 --> 00:10:44,061
OH... YOU MEAN
THE OTHER GUY.

229
00:10:44,144 --> 00:10:45,479
FRANKIE:
I KEEP TEXTING
AND THERE'S NO RESPONSE.

230
00:10:45,562 --> 00:10:47,606
YOU COULD ALWAYS
JUST CALL.

231
00:10:50,067 --> 00:10:52,569
(PHONE RINGS)

232
00:10:52,653 --> 00:10:54,404
LOGAN: FRANKIE?
FRANKIE: LOGAN?

233
00:10:54,488 --> 00:10:55,697
IS THAT YOU?
ARE YOU OKAY?

234
00:10:55,781 --> 00:10:57,157
LOGAN:
UH... I'M SO GLAD YOU CALLED.

235
00:10:57,241 --> 00:10:59,451
UM, THE COPS AREN'T WITH YOU,
ARE THEY?

236
00:10:59,535 --> 00:11:00,786
FRANKIE: NO,
BUT I CAN CALL THEM.
LOGAN: OH, NO, NO. DON'T...

237
00:11:00,869 --> 00:11:02,621
DON'T DO THAT.
IT'S JUST UM...

238
00:11:02,704 --> 00:11:04,498
I STUCK MY NECK OUT FOR HER,
FRANKS,

239
00:11:04,581 --> 00:11:06,458
UH, AND SHE TURNED ON ME.

240
00:11:06,542 --> 00:11:08,544
FRANKIE:
GLORIA?

241
00:11:08,627 --> 00:11:10,420
LOGAN:
YEAH, BECAUSE OF THAT
OTHER GIRL.

242
00:11:10,504 --> 00:11:11,338
FRANKIE: WHAT OTHER GIRL?
LOGAN: NEVERMIND.

243
00:11:11,421 --> 00:11:14,132
I- I NEED A LITTLE MORE MONEY.

244
00:11:14,216 --> 00:11:16,844
NOT MUCH. UH-UH-UM... JUST...
JUST FIVE THOUSAND DOLLARS.

245
00:11:20,222 --> 00:11:23,976
FRANKIE:
SO IT WAS ALL A SCAM?
YOU USED ME?

246
00:11:24,059 --> 00:11:25,644
LOGAN:
OH, ARE WE SERIOUSLY
GONNA DO THIS RIGHT NOW?

247
00:11:25,727 --> 00:11:26,812
I'M SORRY.
I DON'T HAVE TIME FOR THIS.

248
00:11:26,895 --> 00:11:28,897
FRANKIE:
I THOUGHT YOU UM...

249
00:11:28,981 --> 00:11:32,609
LOGAN:
WHAT, THAT I LOVED YOU?
THAT I WANTED TO BE WITH YOU?

250
00:11:32,693 --> 00:11:33,986
YOU'RE JUST SOME STUPID
RICH GIRL

251
00:11:34,069 --> 00:11:35,654
LOOKING FOR A LITTLE
EXCITEMENT.

252
00:11:35,737 --> 00:11:39,366
'KAY, WELL, YOU GOT WHAT
YOU WANTED, DIDN'T YOU?

253
00:11:39,449 --> 00:11:41,535
GLORIA:
HELP! I NEED YOUR HELP!
(BANGING ON DOOR)

254
00:11:41,618 --> 00:11:43,829
PLEASE! PLEASE! HELP!
(BANGING ON DOOR)

255
00:11:43,912 --> 00:11:45,539
(DOOR LOCK UNLATCHES)
SHE JUST... COLLAPSED.

256
00:11:52,754 --> 00:11:54,715
(WEAPON THUMPS INEFFECTIVELY,
GLORIA SCREAMS)

257
00:11:54,798 --> 00:11:57,718
LOGAN:
WHAT THE HELL?!
WHAT'RE YOU DOING?!

258
00:11:57,801 --> 00:11:59,219
GLORIA:
I DON'T KNOW!
I WANT THIS TO BE OVER!

259
00:11:59,303 --> 00:12:01,346
LOGAN:
YEAH?! SO DID I!

260
00:12:01,430 --> 00:12:04,057
BUT YOU THIS DUMB BLONDE
FOLLOW YOU HERE.

261
00:12:04,141 --> 00:12:06,018
WE WERE-WE WERE SO CLOSE
TO GETTING AWAY WITH THIS.

262
00:12:06,101 --> 00:12:07,936
MAYA:
WE?

263
00:12:08,020 --> 00:12:09,188
YOU TWO STAGED
THE KIDNAPPING?!

264
00:12:09,271 --> 00:12:11,732
NOW WHO'S THE DUMB ONE?

265
00:12:11,815 --> 00:12:13,567
WHY DID I GO ALONG
WITH YOUR STUPID PLAN
IN THE FIRST PLACE?

266
00:12:13,650 --> 00:12:14,985
LOGAN:
SO WE COULD BE TOGETHER

267
00:12:15,068 --> 00:12:17,654
WITHOUT YOUR PARENTS
TRYING TO BREAK US UP!

268
00:12:17,738 --> 00:12:19,698
WHERE DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE GOING?

269
00:12:19,781 --> 00:12:22,201
MAYA:
NO, NO, NO. PLEASE.
YOU CAN STILL BE TOGETHER,
JUST LET ME GO.

270
00:12:22,284 --> 00:12:25,120
LOGAN:
YEAH? HOW CAN I TRUST YOU?!
I CAN'T TRUST ANYBODY!

271
00:12:25,204 --> 00:12:28,373
LOGAN, PLEASE.
WE STILL HAVE THE MONEY,
WE CAN JUST RUN AWAY.

272
00:12:28,457 --> 00:12:30,709
LOGAN:
TEN THOUSAND DOLLARS
IS NOT GONNA GET US FAR
WITH THE COPS ON OUR TAIL.

273
00:12:30,792 --> 00:12:33,045
THERE'S GOTTA BE A WAY
WE CAN GET OUTTA THIS.

274
00:12:33,128 --> 00:12:35,422
LOGAN:
YEAH.

275
00:12:35,506 --> 00:12:37,466
WE NEED TO GET RID
OF HER.

276
00:12:37,549 --> 00:12:40,135
MAYA:
(SHAKY BREATH)

277
00:12:40,219 --> 00:12:41,386
MILES:
WE'VE PRINTED OFF
SOME PICS OF MAYA.

278
00:12:41,470 --> 00:12:43,514
ZIG:
PERFECT. LET'S GO.

279
00:12:43,597 --> 00:12:45,682
WINSTON:
NO, WAIT.
THE CITY'S HUGE.

280
00:12:45,766 --> 00:12:47,309
HOW'RE WE GONNA COVER
ALL THAT TERRITORY?

281
00:12:47,392 --> 00:12:48,560
GRACE:
YOU'VE GOT ONE MORE
BODY NOW.

282
00:12:48,644 --> 00:12:51,230
ZOE: YOU CAME?
GRACE: OF COURSE.

283
00:12:51,313 --> 00:12:55,108
MAYA'S MY FRIEND.

284
00:12:55,192 --> 00:12:57,277
ZIG:
OKAY, WHERE-
WHERE DO WE EVEN START?

285
00:12:57,361 --> 00:12:58,862
FRANKIE:
I MIGHT HAVE AN IDEA.

286
00:12:58,946 --> 00:13:00,572
I TALKED TO LOGAN.
THAT'S GLORIA'S BOYFRIEND.

287
00:13:00,656 --> 00:13:02,658
HE MENTIONED ANOTHER GIRL.

288
00:13:02,741 --> 00:13:04,910
MILES: MAYA?
FRANKIE: I THINK SO.
HE SOUNDED DESPERATE.

289
00:13:04,993 --> 00:13:06,995
ZIG:
W-WHAT'S THIS GUY
EVEN CAPABLE OF?

290
00:13:07,079 --> 00:13:10,624
FRANKIE:
I DON'T KNOW. OBVIOUSLY,
I DIDN'T KNOW HIM AT ALL.

291
00:13:10,707 --> 00:13:12,584
GRACE:
GIVE ME YOUR PHONE.

292
00:13:12,668 --> 00:13:14,044
WE MIGHT BE ABLE TO FIGURE OUT
HIS EXACT LOCATION.

293
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:19,174
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON...

294
00:13:19,258 --> 00:13:21,260
DAMN, HIS PHONE'S OFF.

295
00:13:21,343 --> 00:13:22,928
HUNTER:
OKAY, WHAT ABOUT THAT VIDEO
ASKING FOR THE MONEY?

296
00:13:23,011 --> 00:13:25,264
CAN WE LIFT ANY INFORMATION
OFF THAT?

297
00:13:25,347 --> 00:13:28,225
FRANKIE:
I DON'T HAVE A COPY,
BUT IT LOOKED LIKE IT WAS
FILMED IN A WAREHOUSE.

298
00:13:28,308 --> 00:13:30,269
TRISTAN:
THAT SOUNDS LIKE THE PLACE
GLORIA FILMS
HER FROZEN TREAT VIDEOS.

299
00:13:30,352 --> 00:13:31,562
GLORIA: (ON VIDEO)
TODAY'S S'MORES-INSPIRED
FROZEN TREAT RECIPE

300
00:13:31,645 --> 00:13:33,522
COMES FROM SAMANTHA
IN NEW JERSEY.

301
00:13:33,605 --> 00:13:36,233
FRANKIE:
WAIT, IS THAT THE CN TOWER?

302
00:13:36,316 --> 00:13:38,485
ZOE:
IF WE CAN FIND OUT
THE FOCAL LENGTH ON THE CAMERA
THAT SHE USED,

303
00:13:38,569 --> 00:13:41,780
WE CAN FIGURE OUT HOW FAR AWAY
FROM THE CN TOWER SHE WAS
WHEN SHE FILMED IT.

304
00:13:41,864 --> 00:13:43,115
GRACE:
USING THAT FORMULA
WE LEARNED IN SCIENCE CLASS.

305
00:13:43,198 --> 00:13:44,783
NICE.

306
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,452
BUT HOW DO WE FIND
THE FOCAL LENGTH?

307
00:13:47,536 --> 00:13:49,329
ZOE:
WELL, SHE PROBABLY SHOOTS
HER VIDEOS ON A SMARTPHONE.

308
00:13:49,413 --> 00:13:52,332
(COMPUTER KEYS CLACK)

309
00:13:52,416 --> 00:13:54,334
GRACE:
WHICH HAS A FOCAL LENGTH OF...
4.28.

310
00:13:56,795 --> 00:13:59,798
AND THE HEIGHT OF
THE CN TOWER IS...

311
00:13:59,882 --> 00:14:03,135
553.33 METRES.

312
00:14:03,218 --> 00:14:05,846
ZOE:
SO WHEN SHE FILMED IT,
SHE WAS...

313
00:14:05,929 --> 00:14:08,807
15.2 KILOMETRES AWAY,
FACING EAST.

314
00:14:13,228 --> 00:14:14,855
GRACE: THE BLUFFS.
ZOE: THAT'S CLOSE
TO THE OLD SUGAR FACTORY.

315
00:14:15,564 --> 00:14:17,107
ZIG: W-W-WE SHOULD GO.
WINSTON: NO.

316
00:14:17,191 --> 00:14:19,443
WE SHOULD CALL THE COPS.

317
00:14:19,526 --> 00:14:21,945
(DOOR OPENS)
HEY, WE NEED TO GO NOW.

318
00:14:23,864 --> 00:14:27,159
(BAG RUSTLES)

319
00:14:27,242 --> 00:14:29,036
GLORIA:
WHAT ABOUT MAYA?

320
00:14:29,119 --> 00:14:30,954
LOGAN:
WE'LL TIE HER UP,
THEN LEAVE HER IN THE WOODS.

321
00:14:31,038 --> 00:14:32,497
WE'LL BE LONG GONE
BY THE TIME THEY FIND HER.

322
00:14:32,581 --> 00:14:34,791
GLORIA:
SHE COULD DIE.
WE CAN'T DO THAT.

323
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:36,960
MAYA: AGREED.
LOGAN: SHUT UP!
THIS DOESN'T CONCERN YOU!

324
00:14:37,044 --> 00:14:39,254
MAYA: THAT'S DEBATABLE.
LOGAN: I SAID, SHUT UP, OKAY?

325
00:14:39,338 --> 00:14:41,590
(MAYA STRUGGLES)
LOGAN: 'KAY, MOVE!

326
00:14:41,673 --> 00:14:43,300
MAYA:
(SCREAMING) HELP ME!

327
00:14:43,383 --> 00:14:45,093
'KAY, GLORIA! I'LL GET THE CAR,
YOU FINISH TYING HER UP.

328
00:14:48,722 --> 00:14:50,974
MAYA:
(CRYING) GLORIA,
PLEASE DON'T DO THIS.

329
00:14:51,058 --> 00:14:52,809
(CRYING)
PLEASE...

330
00:14:52,893 --> 00:14:54,520
(SHAKY BREATHS)

331
00:14:57,481 --> 00:14:58,315
MALE OFFICER:
THIS IS THE POLICE!

332
00:14:58,398 --> 00:15:00,317
FEMALE OFFICER:
WE'RE COMING IN!

333
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:03,153
MALE OFFICER:
YOU! GET ON THE GROUND!
I SAID GET ON THE GROUND! NOW!

334
00:15:03,237 --> 00:15:04,655
LOGAN:
OKAY! OKAY!
I DIDN'T HURT THEM!

335
00:15:04,738 --> 00:15:06,865
FEMALE OFFICER:
GET ON THE GROUND!

336
00:15:06,949 --> 00:15:07,783
MALE OFFICER: CLEAR!
(SIRENS WAIL OUTSIDE)

337
00:15:07,866 --> 00:15:08,951
MAYA:
(CRYING TEARS OF RELIEF)

338
00:15:13,664 --> 00:15:15,374
MR. HOLLINGSWORTH:
THERE WE GO...
NOW, THANKS TO THIS CLASS,

339
00:15:15,457 --> 00:15:17,543
WE BROUGHT YOUR FRIEND
HOME SAFELY.

340
00:15:17,876 --> 00:15:20,587
IF I HAD MY WAY,
I WOULD GIVE YOU ALL A'S.

341
00:15:20,671 --> 00:15:22,005
MR. BAIN: (LAUGHS)
MR. HOLLINGSWORTH: MR. BAIN?

342
00:15:22,089 --> 00:15:23,924
MR. BAIN:
UH... OH, VERY GOOD,

343
00:15:24,007 --> 00:15:26,426
BUT I THINK WE WILL RELY
ON THE PERFORMANCES
FROM YOUR FINAL EXAMS.

344
00:15:26,510 --> 00:15:27,970
(EVERYONE CLAPS)

345
00:15:32,349 --> 00:15:33,684
TRISTAN:
OKAY.

346
00:15:40,691 --> 00:15:41,859
ZOE: HI, MR. BAIN.
MR. BAIN: HEY.

347
00:15:44,695 --> 00:15:47,614
ZOE:
I KNOW I HAVEN'T BEEN
THE EASIEST STUDENT,

348
00:15:47,698 --> 00:15:50,033
BUT... I WANTED YOU TO KNOW
THAT I LEARNED A LOT.

349
00:15:50,117 --> 00:15:51,493
MR. BAIN:
UH, OBVIOUSLY.

350
00:15:51,577 --> 00:15:54,329
YOU CRACKED THE GLORIA CHIN
CASE BEFORE I DID.

351
00:15:54,413 --> 00:15:57,875
I FANCY MYSELF
AN AMATEUR GUMSHOE.

352
00:15:57,958 --> 00:15:59,209
THAT'S WHY YOU HAD
ALL THOSE MISSING GIRL FILES
IN YOUR TRUCK.

353
00:15:59,293 --> 00:16:01,962
MR. BAIN:
MM-HMM.

354
00:16:02,045 --> 00:16:04,006
I THINK THIS BELONGS
TO YOU.

355
00:16:04,089 --> 00:16:06,758
ZOE:
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

356
00:16:06,842 --> 00:16:09,428
I AM... SO SORRY
I CALLED THE COPS.

357
00:16:09,511 --> 00:16:11,388
MR. BAIN:
APOLOGY ACCEPTED.

358
00:16:11,471 --> 00:16:13,473
JUST REMEMBER THAT APPEARANCES
CAN BE DECEIVING.

359
00:16:13,557 --> 00:16:16,727
IT'S ALWAYS BEST
TO TRUST YOUR GUT.

360
00:16:16,810 --> 00:16:22,316
♪ ...working it out,
trying not to make a sound ♪

361
00:16:22,399 --> 00:16:26,320
♪ Chasing another arrow
of light, ♪

362
00:16:26,403 --> 00:16:29,364
♪ It's almost
the same somehow ♪

363
00:16:29,448 --> 00:16:31,700
(WAVES LAP AT THE SHORE,
PEOPLE CHATTER)

364
00:16:34,912 --> 00:16:37,998
♪ You love another... ♪

365
00:16:38,081 --> 00:16:39,541
CAN WE TALK?

366
00:16:42,586 --> 00:16:44,630
♪ You love another... ♪

367
00:16:44,713 --> 00:16:48,800
LOGAN WAS A JERK.
BUT YOU'RE NOT.

368
00:16:48,884 --> 00:16:52,429
WHICH IS WHY I'M HOPING
YOU'LL GIVE ME SECOND CHANCE?

369
00:16:52,513 --> 00:16:55,974
WINSTON: AT WHAT, FRANKIE?
FRANKIE: US, OBVIOUSLY.

370
00:16:56,099 --> 00:16:58,560
THERE'S NO US ANYMORE.

371
00:16:58,644 --> 00:17:00,562
FRANKIE:
WINSTON, COME ON.
IT'S NOT LIKE I CHEATED.

372
00:17:00,646 --> 00:17:02,147
WINSTON:
NOT WITH YOUR LIPS.

373
00:17:02,231 --> 00:17:06,318
BUT WHAT YOU DID...
WAS WAY WORSE.

374
00:17:06,401 --> 00:17:08,237
SO I'M DONE TALKING.

375
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:11,156
LIKE, FOREVER.

376
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:17,788
♪♪

377
00:17:17,871 --> 00:17:19,414
MAYA:
OOH... YOU'RE HOLDING ME
SO TIGHT.

378
00:17:19,498 --> 00:17:21,416
ZIG:
AND I'M NEVER LETTING GO.

379
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:23,460
HAVE I TOLD YOU HOW HAPPY I AM
TO HAVE YOU IN MY LIFE?

380
00:17:23,544 --> 00:17:26,421
MAYA:
ONLY LIKE A MILLION TIMES.

381
00:17:26,505 --> 00:17:28,340
I WISH EVERYONE
WAS SO LUCKY.

382
00:17:28,423 --> 00:17:30,467
YOU'RE THINKING OF GLORIA?

383
00:17:30,551 --> 00:17:31,844
MAYA:
IF SHE HAD HAD GOOD PEOPLE
IN HER LIFE,

384
00:17:31,927 --> 00:17:35,097
SHE WOULDN'T BE HEADED
TO JUVEY RIGHT NOW.

385
00:17:35,180 --> 00:17:38,350
(SIGHS) OH, I JUST DON'T
WANT THE SAME TO HAPPEN
TO THOSE KIDS I BABYSAT FOR,

386
00:17:38,433 --> 00:17:41,061
WHICH IS WHY I SENT
THEIR MOM A MESSAGE
BEGGING FOR MY JOB BACK.

387
00:17:41,144 --> 00:17:43,188
YOU'LL SAVE THE WORLD,
MAYA MATLIN.

388
00:17:45,858 --> 00:17:47,276
(KISSING)

389
00:17:47,359 --> 00:17:50,404
EVERETT: EW!
LENA: HI, ZIG!

390
00:17:50,487 --> 00:17:52,948
MAYA:
WHAT'RE YOU GUYS
DOING HERE?!

391
00:17:53,031 --> 00:17:55,284
JORDYN:
IT TOOK SOME TIME...

392
00:17:55,367 --> 00:17:57,536
BUT I REALIZED
YOU WERE RIGHT.

393
00:17:57,619 --> 00:17:59,454
UH, I CAN BABYSIT AGAIN?
I'LL BE FREE WHEN SCHOOL
STARTS.

394
00:17:59,538 --> 00:18:02,958
JORDYN:
AH, YOU MIGHT NOT.

395
00:18:03,041 --> 00:18:05,961
I WAS HOPING YOU COULD
HELP ME OUT IN THE STUDIO,

396
00:18:06,044 --> 00:18:09,047
DIGITIZING FILES AND STUFF,
SO I CAN SPEND SOME MORE TIME
WITH THE KIDS.

397
00:18:09,131 --> 00:18:11,466
MAYA:
(SQUEALS EXCITEDLY)

398
00:18:11,550 --> 00:18:12,801
ZIG:
I THINK THAT'S A YES.

399
00:18:12,885 --> 00:18:14,094
JORDYN:
(LAUGHS)

400
00:18:14,178 --> 00:18:17,306
MAYA:
(BREATHY) YES!

401
00:18:18,098 --> 00:18:20,517
THE END.

402
00:18:20,601 --> 00:18:22,644
OH, UM...

403
00:18:22,728 --> 00:18:24,730
EXCEPT FOR ONE THING.

404
00:18:24,813 --> 00:18:26,607
(PEOPLE CHATTER AND SHOUT,
WAVES LAP AT THE SHORE)

405
00:18:26,690 --> 00:18:28,650
YOU SEEM ALL FAR AWAY.

406
00:18:33,864 --> 00:18:37,034
WELL, BECAUSE THERE'S
ONE MORE THING WE NEED TO DO
BEFORE SUMMER'S OVER.

407
00:18:37,117 --> 00:18:40,037
♪ Can you come closer... ♪
(Closer...)

408
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:41,914
♪ And show me
that you're mine ♪

409
00:18:41,997 --> 00:18:43,665
♪ (That you're mine,
that you're mine) ♪

410
00:18:43,749 --> 00:18:46,877
♪ I'm looking for some closure ♪
(Closure...)

411
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:49,338
♪ 'Cause we've been dancing
all night ♪

412
00:18:49,421 --> 00:18:51,381
♪ So tell me if it's real ♪
(RECORD SCRATCHES ABRUPTLY)

413
00:18:51,465 --> 00:18:53,383
(SIGHS)
THAT DIDN'T HAPPEN.

414
00:18:53,467 --> 00:18:55,886
BUT THIS DID.

415
00:18:55,969 --> 00:18:58,013
YOU SEEM ALL FAR AWAY.

416
00:18:58,096 --> 00:19:01,350
(PEOPLE CHATTER,
SEAGULLS CRY)

417
00:19:01,433 --> 00:19:03,560
THERE'S ONE THING I NEED
TO DO BEFORE SUMMER'S OVER.

418
00:19:03,644 --> 00:19:07,272
(TAKES A DEEP BREATH)

419
00:19:07,356 --> 00:19:09,650
(PEOPLE CHATTER,
WAVES LAP AT THE SHORE)

420
00:19:12,319 --> 00:19:13,570
(WAVES LAP,
SEAGULLS CRY)

421
00:19:17,032 --> 00:19:18,659
I'M SORRY FOR
CALLING YOU NAMES...

422
00:19:21,119 --> 00:19:23,247
AND FOR ACTING
LIKE A TOTAL IDIOT.

423
00:19:23,330 --> 00:19:25,582
WE DON'T HAVE TO DO THIS.

424
00:19:25,666 --> 00:19:29,211
WE CAN ACCEPT THAT
WE'RE NOT MEANT BE FRIENDS.

425
00:19:29,294 --> 00:19:31,880
YOU ARE THE MOST
FRUSTRATING PERSON
I HAVE EVER MET.

426
00:19:31,964 --> 00:19:34,466
YOU MAKE FUN OF ME
ALL THE TIME. YOU TELL ME
I'M WRONG. YOU...

427
00:19:34,550 --> 00:19:36,343
YOU SEE THE REAL ME.

428
00:19:36,426 --> 00:19:40,222
THE GIRL I TRY SO HARD
TO HIDE, AND YOU LIKE HER.

429
00:19:40,305 --> 00:19:41,598
I'M SURE OTHER PEOPLE
WOULD TOO.

430
00:19:41,682 --> 00:19:44,560
SOMETIMES YOU MAKE ME FEEL
SO SPECIAL AND...

431
00:19:44,643 --> 00:19:49,022
I'M SCARED THAT IF I LOSE YOU,
I'LL NEVER FEEL THAT WAY AGAIN.

432
00:19:49,106 --> 00:19:51,441
(KISSING)

433
00:19:51,525 --> 00:19:53,652
(PEOPLE CHATTER,
WAVES LAP)

434
00:19:57,781 --> 00:19:59,575
ZOE:
DON'T SAY ANYTHING.

435
00:19:59,658 --> 00:20:02,077
I'VE RUSHED THINGS BEFORE
AND I DON'T WANNA RUSH THIS.

436
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:06,039
SCHOOL STARTS IN A WEEK.
LET'S TALK THEN.

437
00:20:06,123 --> 00:20:09,293
♪ Can you come closer ♪
(Closer...)

438
00:20:09,376 --> 00:20:11,170
♪ And show me
that you're mine ♪

439
00:20:11,253 --> 00:20:13,088
♪ (That you're mine,
that you're mine...) ♪

440
00:20:13,172 --> 00:20:16,133
♪ I'm looking for some closure ♪
(Closure...)

441
00:20:16,216 --> 00:20:18,135
♪ 'Cause we've been dancing
all night ♪

442
00:20:18,218 --> 00:20:21,722
♪ So tell me if it's real,
baby ♪

443
00:20:21,805 --> 00:20:23,348
♪ Tell me if it's not ♪

444
00:20:23,432 --> 00:20:25,225
♪ (Not, not, not,
tell me if it's not...) ♪

445
00:20:25,309 --> 00:20:28,979
♪ This is how I feel, baby, ♪

446
00:20:29,062 --> 00:20:32,357
♪ I hope it never stops ♪
(Never stops, stops, stops...)

447
00:20:32,441 --> 00:20:33,650
(RECORD SCRATCHES ABRUPTLY,
TRISTAN SNIFFLES)

448
00:20:33,734 --> 00:20:37,863
AH. SORRY. I AM JUST A SUCKER
FOR A HAPPY ENDING.

449
00:20:37,946 --> 00:20:39,156
BUT IT'S NOT OVER.

450
00:20:39,239 --> 00:20:41,617
YOU WANT REAL DRAMA?

451
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:43,994
COME BACK WHEN SCHOOL STARTS.
IT ONLY GETS CRAZIER.

452
00:20:44,077 --> 00:20:46,121
TRUST ME.

453
00:20:46,205 --> 00:20:48,415
YOUR NEW BESTIE, TRIS.
(DANCE MUSIC RESUMES PLAYING)

